        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You wanted nothing more then to pull beauty from marble, to pull the suple breath of life from the cold, unforgiving stone. It was a dying craft, giving way to sexier mediums like painting or photography, but that wasn't for you. For you, only the animated from the inannimate could feed your passion. You studied, you apprentice, but it was never enough.  You were never good enough. But you heard of a Master, far away in Rome, that would only take the most dedicated of students, but for a price.  It didn't matter, you had to go. You traveled to the ancient city where you spent years seeking out this master scuplture. You found any amount who pretneded, but you knew they were never who you sought.  It wasn't you who found them, though; it was he who found you.  For teaching you all he knew, you only had to give him your soul.  Was this the devil?!  No, it was perhaps worse: it was a vampire.  But his words were honied and his works entranced you like nothing you'd ever seen in the waking world.  You gave yourself over to him, and lived to die for art.  Kindred society is not really so different from mortals, only that everything moves at a pace all its own. And even as your work grew, you found yourself unsatisfied with it. Was this all there was?  You started to hear whispers of Toreador who could sculpt... flesh.  But they had all been destroyed, hadn't they?  ...maybe not."
        ],
